            [
                new("What is Digi-ID?", "A passwordless authentication protocol for DigiByte. Websites show a <code>digiid://</code> QR code — you scan it with your wallet, approve the domain, and the wallet signs a cryptographic challenge. No passwords needed."),
                new("How do I use Digi-ID?", "Go to the <b>ID</b> tab → scan the Digi-ID QR code from a website (or paste the <code>digiid://</code> URI). Review the domain and callback URL, then tap <b>Approve</b>. You'll see a 3-step progress animation (signing → sending → verifying) and a success confirmation with the address used."),
                new("Is Digi-ID safe?", "Yes. Each website gets a unique derived key (path <code>m/13'/siteIndex'/0'/0</code>). Your main wallet keys are never exposed. Only a cryptographic signature is sent — no private data leaves your device. The confirmation panel explains this before you approve."),
                new("What happens during signing?", "Three steps happen in sequence: <b>1)</b> Your wallet derives a site-specific private key and signs the challenge URI with a compact recoverable signature. <b>2)</b> The signed response is sent to the website's callback server (via our API proxy to avoid browser CORS issues). <b>3)</b> The server verifies the signature and logs you in."),
                new("What does 'rejected the signature' mean?", "The website's server could not verify the cryptographic signature. This usually means the QR code or URI has <b>expired</b> — most Digi-ID challenges are valid for only a few minutes. Scan a <b>fresh QR code</b> from the website and try again."),
                new("What does 'Could not reach server' mean?", "The authentication server is unreachable. This could be a <b>network issue</b> on your end, or the website's server may be down. Check your internet connection and try again. If the problem persists, the website may be experiencing downtime."),
                new("Can I retry a failed authentication?", "Yes. When authentication fails, tap <b>Try Again</b> to re-sign and resend without needing to re-scan the QR code. If the challenge has expired, you'll need to scan a new one from the website."),
                new("Which sites support Digi-ID?", "Any website that implements the Digi-ID protocol. Examples include <b>DigiScope</b> (<code>digiscope.me</code>) and other DigiByte community services. Look for a \"Login with Digi-ID\" button or QR code on supported sites."),
            ]),

